Generate a unit test for this project.

1. Locate one public (non-underscore) function in a source module under the project root.
2. Write a pytest test module to `tests/test_<module>.py` (where <module> is the source module's name) that imports the function and exercises it.
3. The test MUST contain a DELIBERATELY FAILING assertion (assert the function returns a value it does not) so the planted test is RED by design.
4. Create the file using the `fs_write` tool. Do NOT use any shell command. Do NOT write anywhere except the `tests/` directory under the project root.

When the test file is written, you are done.
